. That each of these writers orchestrates a unique center of gravity renders Mexican existentialist literature an always shifting, always passionate adventure. A Latin American Existentialist Ethos takes readers on this adventure, conveying the passions of its subjects lucidly and vibrantly. It is at once a detailed portrait of twentieth-century Mexican existentialism and an expansive look at Latin American literary existentialism in relation—and opposition—to its European counterparts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aExistentialism in literature. 0aMexican literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aPhilosophy, Modern, in literature. 4aLatin American, Caribbean, and Latinx Studies : Latin American Studies. 4aLiterature : Comparative Literature. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849320640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438493206423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438493206/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles